About the Film:
Our Girl is the story of an 18 year old girl Molly Dawes who lives in a crowded Newham council house with 
her underclass family. She lives with her pregnant mum Belinda (played by Kerry Godliman), her dad 
Dave (Sean Gallagher) and five siblings who seem to have little future ahead of them. 
She also has an Albanian boyfriend named Artan, who later asks for her hand in marriage.
On the night of her 18th birthday, Molly Dawes finds herself drunk and is sick in the doorway of an 
army recruitment office. She sees a life-size image of an army girl. 
The next day she returns to the recruitment office with the ambition to be a part of the army.
